<h2>Overview</h2><p>Upgrading your Jeep Wrangler's hardware can result in noticeable changes in performance, especially regarding the doors. The TMR Customs Delrin hinge liners are a popular modification among Wrangler owners for their durability and improved functionality. However, one common issue that may arise after the installation is misalignment of the door strikers, which can affect how your doors close. This tutorial will guide you through the simple adjustment process to get your doors back in working order.</p> <h2>What This Covers</h2><p>In this article, we'll cover the adjustment process for Jeep Wrangler door strikers after installing TMR Customs Delrin hinge liners. You’ll learn about the typical symptoms of misaligned strikers, the tools you’ll need, and the step-by-step procedure to correct the alignment for optimal door functionality.</p> <h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol> <li><strong>Identify the Issue:</strong> Once your hinge liners are installed, check if the door closes with a harsher sound or does not latch properly. Look for shiny spots on the striker, which indicate excessive contact or misalignment.</li> <li><strong>Gather Tools:</strong> For this adjustment, you will need a T4 and T5 Torx screwdriver. These are essential for loosening the striker assembly.</li> <li><strong>Loosen the Striker:</strong> Carefully loosen the screws holding the door striker in place. Do so without completely removing them to allow for adjustment.</li> <li><strong>Adjust the Striker Position:</strong> With the assembly loosened, slide the striker up slightly to align it better with the latch. It's only a minor adjustment, usually just a few millimeters.</li> <li><strong>Test the Door:</strong> Close the door to see if it latches smoothly. If needed, make further minor adjustments until the door closes effortlessly.</li> <li><strong>Repeat for All Doors:</strong> Once satisfied with the first door, repeat the process for the remaining doors on your Jeep.</li> </ol> <h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul> <li>Keep track of any adjustments you make for each door to ensure consistency.</li> <li>If your doors still do not align properly after adjustments, double-check the hinge liner installation.</li> <li>Consider lubricating the latch and striker with a silicone spray to improve performance further.</li> </ul> <h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Adjusting the door strikers after installing TMR Customs Delrin hinge liners is a quick and simple process that can significantly enhance your Jeep's door functionality. With just a few tools and adjustments, you can ensure a smooth, quiet closure every time. Don't overlook these small fixes; they can make a huge difference in your driving experience.</p>

